On Dec 4, 2015, 21:59 -0600, Matthew Johnson<matthew at anandabits.com>, wrote:
> I think this idea scratches at the surface of a problem with initializers that definitely merits some attention.Boilerplate is common in initializers which can lead to types that dont allow as much flexibility to callers as might be desirable.
